<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3639] C# Thrift library forces TLS 1.0, thwarting TLS 1.2 usage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3639</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TTLSSocket.cs.setupTLS() uses SslProtocols.Tls, which forces TLS 1.0.  I suspect this was originally done to prevent SSLv2 from working against a poorly configured server, but now prevents working against a TLS 1.2 server, thus decreasing security.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since PCI-DSS requires removing anything less than TLS 1.2 by June, this is a critical issue for those of us working in that environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
